title: Grateful Dead Live at Giants Stadium on 1992-06-15

Set 1

Hell In A Bucket, Sugaree, The Same Thing, Tennessee Jed, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Bird Song

Set 2

Box Of Rain, Saint Of Circumstance-> So Many Roads-> Terrapin Station-> Drums-> Jam*-> I Need A Miracle*-> Standing On the Moon*-> Throwing Stones-> Not Fade Away*, E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

* w/ Steve Miller, guitar.  Steve Miller Band Opened.

reviews.review_text:
Thx Thank you for posting this show!
Gil

The show that turned me off. I was at this show and it was my least favorite show I've been to. The firs set was very short only six songs. Then they took a 45 minute break. The second set looks impressive but the songs were just blah. It seemed like they were just trudging through each song trying to get to the end. Also I'm not the biggest fan of the MIDI guitar sound. I think it sounds cheesy. Drums was the saving grace for this show. I wouldn't see another show until 3-23-95. However, This recording sounds great!!!

Steve miller For me the highlights here are when Steve Miller accompanies them.Although his guitar is a little quite, he is smokin, and a good addition.Jerry rises to the occasion and does some great solos in those songs as well.
